Constructive Feedback for Managers: Giving Feedback Effectively
Description: The animated video explains why feedback is crucial and how the tools, techniques, and strategies that a manager uses when giving feedback have a huge impact on employee engagement.

Title: Digital Leadership with IDA
Description: A learning offer for managers who want to deal intensively with the potentials of digitalisation and who want to shape teamwork, communication and management with IDA. In addition, participants are invited to a community for peer learning.

Title: Conferencia LACNIC 34 - LACNOG 2020
Description: LACNIC 34 - LACNOG 2020 es un evento con calificados expositores de Internet de la región y el mundo y una amplia oferta de capacitaciones y talleres técnicos. Habrán presentaciones de elevado nivel técnico en relación a casos de éxito de operaciones de redes, Internet de las cosas, redes comunitarias, despliegue de IPv6, arquitectura de Internet, servicios de valor agregado, intercambio de tráfico, entre otros asuntos relevantes.

Title: Nesta: Innovation Brokerage
Description: Innovation usually is the result of collaboration and the exchange of ideas of different people connected by intermediaries. This brand new report looks into innovation brokerage and offers policy recommendations how to support and make use of these intermediaries.

Title: Cómo ser equipo humano en el futuro digital
Description: Los humanos ya no somos valorados por nuestra creatividad, dice el teórico de los medios Douglas Rushkoff: en un mundo dominado por la tecnología digital, ahora solo somos valorados por nuestros datos. En una charla apasionada, Rushkoff nos insta a dejar de usar la tecnología para optimizar a las personas para el mercado y comenzar a usarla para construir un futuro centrado en nuestros valores predigitales de conexión, creatividad y respeto. Únete al 'Equipo Humano'. Encuentra a los demás , dice. Hagamos juntos el futuro que siempre quisimos.

Title: Cursos sobre competencias digitales
Description: Una série de 6 cursos ofrecidos por Microsoft que ayudarán a los usuarios a desarrollar habilidades digitales o mejorar sus competencias. Los cursos presentarán entre otras cosas: conocimientos IT básicos, creación y gestion de contenido digital y comunicación en línea.

Title: Help-Each-Other Community
Description: An IDA community, which serves as an exchange platform for topics such as Microsoft Teams, Microsoft Planner, Room Owner, IDA Projects, IDA Communities. Here you can find help and share your knowledge with others.

Title: UNLEASH World Conférence
Description: La 7ème édition du salon UNLEASH World, le plus grand salon mondial dédié à l’avenir du travail et des technologies RH, aura lieu les 22 et 23 octobre prochains à Paris. Pendant 2 jours, le salon proposera un programme de conférences menées par des intervenants de plus de 120 pays pour discuter de l’avenir du secteur, de sa transformation digitale, de l’industrie 4.0, des solutions IA, des nouvelles techniques de leadership et bien plus encore.

Title: KuF Ambassador and Mentoring Program
Description: Soutien à la coopération et au leadership dans le monde du travail numérique : des ambassadeurs et des mentors accompagnent les équipes et les managers et diffusent les principes, les méthodes et les exemples pratiques du KuF afin de réfléchir et de développer les comportements de coopération et de leadership dans le contexte de travail respectif.

Title: John Maeda: comment l'art, la technologie et le design guident les dirigeants créatifs
Description: John Maeda, le Président de l'Ecole du Design de Rhode Island, nous raconte dans ce TED Talk toute une vie de travail dans l'art, le design, et la technologie. Il termine par une description de la direction créative dans l'avenir.

Title: Navigator for the Conception and Purchase of Digital and IT services - for Programs, OU and Country Offices
Description: The Navigator provides an overview of the process steps and contact persons involved in successful, effective and secure IT and digital services: From brainstorming and selecting the right service to tendering, purchasing and controlling.

Title: Digital Pioneers (DE)
Description: Kollegiale Beratung zu neuen Kollaborations- und Kommunikationstools (z.B. IDA, MS Teams etc.) durch digital fitte Mitarbeitende (Digital Pioneers). Die Mulitplikator*innen können Dir weiterhelfen, auch IDA-Partner*innen (IPA) und Digitalisierungspartner*innen (DiPa) in Ihrer Einheit/Landesbüro.

Title: Digital Pioneers (EN)
Description: Collegial consulting on new collaboration and communication tools (e.g. IDA, MS Teams etc.) by digital fit employees (Digital Pioneers). The multipliers can help you, also IDA partners (IPA) and digitalisation partners (DiPa) in your unit/country office.

Title: DMS: Basics - Working with Documents
Description:
Take this webinar if you want to get a first insight into working with the document management
system of GIZ (DMS).

Description:
This offer is aimed at employees in the field structure who are responsible for the document management system (DMV) in
their organisational Units.

Title: DMS: Search Successfully
Description: Take this webinar to get basic knowledge of the GIZ Document Management System (DMS) and how to search successfully.

Title: Help-Each-Other Wiki
Description: Eine IDA.Community, die als Austauschplattform für Themen wie z.B. Microsoft Teams, Microsoft Planner, Room Owner, IDA Projects, IDA Communities dient. Hier findest Du Hilfe und kannst Dein Wissen an andere weitergeben.

Title: How To Use GIZ-Apps (EN)
Description: This IDA Wiki is a preparation of different offers and learning contents for GIZ-internal digital applications, such as Excel lists, YouTube videos, PDF instructions etc.

Title: IDA & Office 365 Training (EN)
Description: Overview page for all online introductory trainings and consultation hours around IDA & Office 365 applications, e.g. introduction into the use of MS Teams, in IDA.Projects and IDA.Communities or into the role of the Room Owner

Title: IDA.Communities Basics Overview Page
Description: Selection of links introducing users to IDA.communities, mainly from the IDA Help-Each-Other Community.

Title: Introduction to GIZ's Digital Collaboration Tools
Description: During the IT introduction day you will get an insight into the IT tools that GIZ uses for cooperation & communication, e.g. MS Teams, Planner, Outlook, Sharepoint-based Ida.Communities/Countries/Org.Units or Skype4Business, as well as DMS and OneDrive

Title: Microsoft Digital Literacy Courses
Femmes Africaines Dans Le Leadership - Leader Dans L'ère Numérique
Description: Le monde d'aujourd'hui est alimenté par la technologie numérique et nous touche tous. La conférence annuelle des femmes africaines dans le Leadership à Londres prévue le 8 septembre 2020 (reporté jusqu'au nouvel ordre) va rassembler les experts de premier plan et axés sur le continent sur les questions touchant les entreprises émergentes, établies et celles qui ciblent l'Afrique. Aussi, un forum de discussion et d'action pour le leadership 21C en Afrique sera organisé autour des questions de l'importance et la pertinence de la technologie pour les organisations; qu'ils soient basés sur la technologie ou non.

Title: Kurse zur digitalen Kompetenz von Microsoft
Article: Why You Can’t Buy A Digital Workplace
Description: Digital workplace is a concept, not a product. Creating digital workplaces therefore requires a fundamental change in thinking about workplaces, not just buying software suites. This article helps to understand the definition of a digital workplace.

Title: How To Use GIZ-Apps (EN)
Description: This IDA Wiki is a preparation of different offers and learning contents for GIZ-internal digital applications, such as Excel lists, YouTube videos, PDF instructions etc.

Title: Microsoft Digital Literacy Courses
Redesigning 925
Description: Pekka Pohjakallio and Saku Tuominen conducted Project 925, a year long close study of 9 Finnish workplaces. Their Workbook presents models, tools and lessons learned from this long-term study. The videos give some insights into the results of the study.

Title: Secure Mobile Working
Description: Secure work also means that our data is protected. Especially when we work remotely, there are security precautions such as multi factor authentication and mobile device management (MFA/MDM).

Title: Skype for Business Basics
Description: This selection of links lead you to short Skype for Business introductory online tutorials.

Title: The Way We Work
Description: This is a series of 8 short videos, curated by TED: Practical wisdom on how to thrive amid changing workplace conventions.

Title: The Workplace Experience Revolution Part 2: Do New Workplaces Work?
Description: Report of a study conducted with 557,959 employee responses providing assessments of 3,932 workplaces worldwide. Workplace redesigns do not always lead to positive change, the report also asks for reasons why.

Title: Center for Humane Technology: A New Agenda For Tech
Description: In this lecture, Tristan Harris offers a diagnosis for the many problems generated by the extractive attention economy as well as a new path forward for producing technology that is aligned with humanity.

Title: Cooperation and Team Management (Academy Course)
Description: As a specialist (without disciplinary leadership responsibility) you cooperate close with employees and coordinate them technically. This course will help you to show how successful cooperation and management of your team can be achieved in order to reach common goals.

Title: Digital Wellbeing in the Twenty-First Century
Description: Report of the Horizon2020 funded DSI4EU project around Digital Social Innovation: This report summarizes the interconnection between technological developments and individual wellbeing and health.

Title: Foresight on new and emerging occupational safety and health risks associated with digitalisation by 2025
Description: In-depth report by the European Agency for Healthy and Safety at Work examinig the risks and foresighting development until 2025.

Title: Healthy Remote Work
Description: To ensure that mobile work is both successful and healthy, the Medical Service and the Corporate Health Management have collected helpful tips and information on this topic.

Title: How To Build A Happy Team
Description: Recording of a workshop hosted by Apolitical: Participants learned how internal cultures have successfully changed to improve mental health, how they themselves can be part of and build a happy team, and what comes within their responsibility as a colleague.

Title: Human Systems: HS 101 Self Study
Description: Self Study Course to gain knowledge, awareness, and instruments for changing the social games that people play around you; and redesigning organisations, social networks, group practices, democratic mechanisms, etc.

Title: Marie Forleo: Decade in Review
Description: 3-part video series that guides users through simple tasks that create awareness and mindfulness of one's needs, wishes and accomplishments over the last decade - and helps make a plan for the next one.

Title: Organising Your Work
Description: This article provides tips and best practices on how to organise work well.

Title: Technology and Health
Description: Being overly connected can cause psychological problems such as distraction, narcissism, expectation of immediate satisfaction and even depression. On the physical side, it can cause vision problems, hearing loss and neck tension. Fortunately, precautions can be taken.

Title: Ueber Product Podcast: Courtney Hemphill – Psychological Safety at Work
Description: Markus Andrezak interviews Courtney Hemhill on psychological safety at work: Why work in the digital sphere needs empathy and self-awareness, and how to practice that.

Title: Etiquette for MS Teams
Description: Colleagues from the Health Services team authored this very useful Etiquette for MS Teams. Check out the english pdf for a quick impression but also find versions in docx and pptx in four languages in the zip file.

Title: Collaboration Supercards
Description: Deck of 24 cards to communicate visually during online meetings. Use the cards to give each other visual clues during your online meetings.

Title: Collaboration Superpowers: Work Together Anywhere
Description: The Work Together Anywhere Workshop is designed to share experiences and learn how to avoid miscommunications, increase comraderie, run problem-free meetings where everyone contributes and inspire continuous improvement.

Title: GIZ Social Media Handbook
Description: Corporate Communications and the Sector Department will launch a comprehensive Social Media Handbook, addressing many relevant issues for GIZ regarding Social Media and providing hands-on advice for its application

Title: MS Teams Room Owner Training
Description: Two webinars recorded by the IDA Team introducing Room Owners (for MS Teams) into their role.

Title: Social Media Consultation Hour by Corporate Communications
Description: Regular consultation hour on the use of social media by GIZ.

Title: Social Media Guidelines
Description: Basic and short list of poignant principles, binding for all GIZ staff members

Title: Social Media - Trend Topic on the Digital Gateway
Description: This is an overview page about social media. Here you will find many useful links and tips for a professional use of social media.

Title: Mindful Minutes
Description: Mindful Minutes is not necessarily about setting up a feel-good program, but rather about giving all of us at GIZ an understanding of concrete approaches to resilience through the means of practices and tools for balancing, self-management and -regulation.

Title: Cours sur la culture numérique de Microsoft
Digital Pioneer Community (EN)
Description: The Digital Pioneer Community on IDA contains a lot of learning content, as well as a learning café series (webinars) for Digital Pioneers.

Title: How To Use GIZ-Apps (DE): IDA-Wiki de la Academia (AIZ) y el equipo de IDA, DIGITS
Description: No Description

Title: Data Protection WBT
Description: Mandatory web-based training providing essential knowledge on the topic.

Title: Umgang mit bösartigen E-Mails / Sicheres Surfen im Internet
Description: In diesem verpflichtenden webbasierten Training erhältst Du grundlegende Informationen darüber, wie Sie gefährliche E-Mails und Internetseiten erkennen können. Dies erfolgt zunächst mit einem kurzen theoretischen Input. In Quizfragen können Sie Ihr Wissen prüfen.

Title: Dealing with Malicious Emails / Safe Surfing in the Internet
Description: In this mandatory web-based training, you will receive basic information on how to detect dangerous emails and websites. This is done first with a short theoretical input. In quiz questions you can test your knowledge.

Title: Different Online Courses about Cyber Security
Description: The learning platform Udemy offers online training courses on digital security and a general overview about cyber security and data privacy.

Title: Digital Security
Description: This course deals with contents of the topics digital security and data security. It includes tools and methods for digital security as well as the recognition and handling of digital risks.

Title: Electronic Frontier Foundation: Surveillance Self-Defense
Description: This is an interactive guide from EFF to protect you from online surveillance. It includes basic texts to find out how online surveillance works; tool guides for EFF's pick of the best, most secure applications as well as links to more detailed information, and security scenarios.

Title: GIZ Handbook on IT Security
Description: The GIZ handbook is a short introduction to the GIZ security standards (e.g. phishing e-mails, password management). You can subscribe to a monthly e-mail IT security tip and access GIZ information pages and external information sources.

Title: GIZ Handreichung zur IT-Sicherheit
Description: Die GIZ-Handreichung ist eine kurze Einführung in die Sicherheitsstandards der GIZ (z.B. Phishing E-Mails, Passwortmanagement). Du kannst hier einen monatlichen E-Mail IT-Sicherheitstipp abonnieren und zu Informationsseiten der GIZ und externen Informationsquellen gelangen.

Title: Intranetsite from DIGITS on IT Security
Description: DIGITS intranet site contains general information on the topic of IT security.

Title: Tactical Tech: Data Detox Kit
Description: The Data Detox Kit is a guide to increase your online privacy, digital security and wellbeing. It offers simple steps you can take towards a more balanced and healthier digital lifestyle.

Title: A Manager's Guide to Healthy Leadership
Description: The guide points to the positive influence that management and leadership can have on employees’ physical, mental and social well-being. It creates clarity about the manager’s role and explores options for fulfilling their responsibilities.

Title: artop: Effective Facilitation of Team and Project Meetings
Description: Effective Facilitation of Team- and Project Meetings teaches how to develop moderation concepts and successfully implement them in team and project meetings to ensure a goal-oriented and efficient approach to these types of communication and effectively deal with the dynamics in the group.

Title: Digital Leadership: David Logan-Tribal Leadership
Description: This TED-Ed Talk summarizes the book Tribal Leadership by David Logan. Main thesis: Organisational culture is the key factor for organisational performance and success, and leaders must know how to shape, design, measure and change organisational culture.

Title: Digital Leadership: Haufe Akademie: Digital Transformation Manager Compact Programme
Description: Participants learn methods and tools for the development of digital strategies and business models, personal development to become a digital leader or in the field of innovation and change management, and receive additional process and IT know-how for digital transformation.

Title: Digital Leadership: Hyper Island - Leading Teams in the Digital Age
Description: Leading Teams in the Digital Age is an online course which teaches a variety of methods and tools for culture, collaboration and leadership in times of change and complexity.

Title: Digital Leadership: Massive Open Online Dialogue (MOOD) on Innovation
Description: The MOOD provides insights into contemporary digital leadership from different perspectives. Geared towards GIZ's managers, the recordings of the webinars are provided to everyone.

Title: Digital Leadership: Radical Candor - Be a Kick-Ass Boss Without Losing Your Humanity
Description: The book, blog, podcast and training offers are based on the idea that a leader has three key responsibilities: creating a culture of feedback (praise and criticism), building a cohesive team, and achieving results you’re all proud of. It is the concept of “Radical Candor”.

Title: Digital Leadership: The Dawn of System Leadership
Description: This very influential article by Peter Senge et al., published in the Stanford Social Innovation Review, deals with the issue of leadership in times of constant change.

Title: Giving & Receiving Feedback Is Difficult – Here’s How to Do It Right
Description: This article summarizes research and practical tools for giving and receiving feedback in contructive ways.

Title: Good Digital Leadership at GIZ
Description: This handout summarizes the skillset of good digital leadership at GIZ, published by HR and Career Development.

Title: How to Give Feedback the Right Way
Description: This article and poster explain the COIN formula (Context - Observation - Impact - Next) for giving feedback. Moreover, you get some tips on phrasing and body language.

Title: Leading Remote and Virtual Teams
Description: This course is an opportunity for leaders looking to strengthen their leadership skills in order to support their team successfully and enable excellent collaborations across long distances. Many of AIZ’s programmes are implemented in fragile and challenging environments.

Title: LinkedIn Learning: Enhancing Team Innovation
Description: Learn how to incorporate innovation and creativity into your workplace, in this course with leadership coach Gemma Leigh Roberts. Discover how to create a space for innovation to thrive, nurture new ideas, learn from challenges, and build room for experimentation and play.

Title: Management 3.0
Description: Management 3.0 serves with practical, hands on and tangible tools and management games to foster transformational change within teams, companies and on a personal level as well as to increase employee motivation.

Title: Management 3.0: Rewards and Incentives
Description: Management 3.0 is a leadership methodology, four books, and a series of workshops given by licensed change facilitators. This e-learning course teaches the design of a reward system that supports intrinsic motivation and encourages healthy behaviors instead of driving people to pursue rewards.

Title: Mind Tools: Giving Feedback
Description: This article is about giving feedback in a constructive way. It addresses the question: Why and how to give feedback?

Title: Sheila Heen: How to Use Others' Feedback to Learn and Grow
Description: Tedx Talk that emphasizes that for feedback to be effective and support growth, it is not only important to learn how to give feedback, but also how to receive it.

Title: Achieving Africa’s Digital Transformation is an Ambition that Requires Game-Changing Cooperation
Description: The World Bank and IMF strongly support the African Union's new agenda for digital transformation and the Digital Moonshot initiative.

Title: All Africa Digital Economy Moonshot
Description: With the aim to digitally connect every individual, business and government in Africa by 2030, the African Union and the World Bank Group, has embarked on an ambitious journey - a “moonshot” that will help countries accelerate progress and bring high-speed connectivity to all.

Title: Collaborative Innovation & the Better Together Award
Description: This webinar covers the topic of “Collaborative Innovation” which is a GIZ financed measure to explore new ways of cooperation between GIZ and innovation ecosystems. The Better Together Award is an international competition seeking collaborative innovations solving local climate challenges.

Title: Fostering Collaborative Innovation for Digital Solutions
Description: The GIZ financed measure Collaborative Innovation for Digital Solutions seeks ways and means how to collaborate better with innovative ecosystems and tech startups. This presentation explains the objectives of this measures and initial insights into this field of action.

Title: Ghana Entrepreneurship Ecosystem Analysis
Description: This study by consultants Koltai and Company for the Department for International Development (DFID) on Ghana of 2013 may appear a bit old; however, a study on frontrunner Ghana may provide valuable advice for countries with nascent or emerging tech ecosystems.

Title: Guide for Mapping the Entrepreneurial Ecosystem
Description: This extensive guide provides insights into the mapping of local entrepreneurial ecosystems - including e.g. tech start-ups - that you may want to cooperate with for more innovative and effective project delivery.

Title: International Development Innovation Alliance
Description: IDIA is a unique collaboration platform that brings together the senior leadership from the innovation teams, labs and departments of some of the world's leading development agencies.

Title: LinkedIn Learning: Enhancing Team Innovation
Description: Learn how to incorporate innovation and creativity into your workplace, in this course with leadership coach Gemma Leigh Roberts. Discover how to create a space for innovation to thrive, nurture new ideas, learn from challenges, and build room for experimentation and play.

Title: MIT CIO: Cooperation vs. Competition in the Digital Ecosystem
Description: Summary of MIT Sloans 2016 CIO Symposium, focused on what digital ecosystems are and how we navigate them. Includes many links, serves as an interesting introduction.

Title: Official Channel and Hashtag for the High-Level Panel on Digital Cooperation in 2019 @UNSGdigicoop #DigitalCooperation  Twitter
Description: Ressources from the High-Level Panel on Digital Cooperation shared on Twitter. An independent panel of 20 experts convened by the UN Secretary General to advance a dialogue on strengthening international cooperation in the digital age.

Title: UN Science Policy Business Forum Discussion Paper: The Case for a Digital Ecosystem for the Environment
Description: This is a discussion paper on why a global digital ecosystem is necessary, how it can be achieved, and what initiatives and projects are out there already. Short summary available here. https://medium.com/@UNDP/the-pressing-need-for-a-global-digital-ecosystem-aa10a9f8df56

Title: Understanding Entrepreneurial Ecosystems through Social Network Analysis (SNA)
Description: This analysis on Uganda's entrepreneurial ecoystem by Credit Suisse, Swiss Contact and Amarin Financial Groups provides  insights into the functioning of emerging ecosystems and their dynamics.

Title: Understanding Innovation Ecosystems: A Framework for Joint Analysis and Action
Description: Whether at the municipal level, in places such as Medellín, Colombia and Guadalajara, México, or the national level in Rwanda, South Africa, or India, MIT D-Lab sees governments, multi-laterals, donors, and civil society actors embarking on initiatives to strengthen local innovation ecosystems.

Title: ValueLinks 2.0 - Introduction to the Methodology for the Promotion of Value Chains
Description: ValueLinks methodology aims to improve the understanding of the value chain and its development as a structural change of the market-oriented economy. This course is not specifically geared towards the digital economy but may provide useful insights about how to cooperate with the private sector.

Title: UN High-Level Panel on Digital Cooperation
Description: The High-Level Panel on Digital Cooperation was convened by the UN Secretary-General to provide recommendations on how the international community could work together to optimize the use of digital technologies and mitigate the risks.

Title: Collaboration Superpowers: Podcast
Description: This podcast with almost 250 episodes deals with remote work, interesting interviews, useful tool tips and great storytelling.

Title: Collaboration Superpowers: Remote Meetings Masterclass
Description: This is a workshop for facilitators of online meetings, workshops, and other events; for high-level managers and coaches working with remote colleagues and/or team members who are enthusiastic about improving productivity and day-to-day communication with their remote colleagues.

Title: Effective Facilitation of Team and Project Meetings by artop
Description: Effective Facilitation of Team- and Project Meetings teaches how to develop moderation concepts and successfully implement them in team and project meetings to ensure a goal-oriented and efficient approach to these types of communication and effectively deal with the dynamics in the group.

Title: Facilitate Pro: Designing Interactive Webinars
Description: The one-way nature of most webinars and web conferences misses an opportunity to engage an audience and draw on the wisdom of the group as well as the knowledge of the guest speaker, pitchman or trainer. Julia Young shares tips on designing interactive webinars.

Title: Facilitating Online Meetings
Description: Online meetings can be a lot of fun! Here are a few ideas to make your meetings exciting, educational, and effective. You get a sample agenda and tools for the facilitation of successful online meetings.

Title: How to facilitate Successful Online Workshops - Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: This is a comprehensive webinar and toolkit for becoming a successful online workshop host.

Title: HowSpace: The Ultimate Guide to Digital Facilitation
Description: This guide is an interactive collection of background information, tips, tools and techniques. It includes a link to the HowSpace ebook.

Title: Online Courses at Lucid Meeting School
Description: This is a collection of online courses around facilitating successful meetings.

Title: SessionLab: Online Tools for Workshop Planning and Meeting Facilitation
Description: This is a list of 25 free online tools for workshop planning and meeting facilitation: surveys, document sharing, video conferencing, online whiteboards, task management, note taking, session agenda planning and classroom engagement.

Title: Successful Facilitation - Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: This is a comprehensive toolkit for successful facilitation.

Title: Online-Treffen moderieren
Description: Online-Meetings können viel Spaß machen! Hier sind ein paar Ideen, wie Du Deine Treffen spannend, lehrreich und effektiv gestalten können. Du erhältst eine Beispiel-Agenda und Werkzeuge für die Moderation erfolgreicher Online-Meetings.

Title: Book: Reinventing Organisations
Description: Book, video series, P2P learning platform and wiki around Reinventing Organisations, the groundbreaking and best-selling book that introduced teal organisations.

Title: Enlivening Edge
Description: Enlivening Edge has an online community, magazine, a newsletter and a podcast series around new work with topics such as holacracy, b corps and management 3.0.

Title: Human-Centered Organizational Governance
Description: Weekly newsletter, extensive resource collection (books, videos and list of successful transforming organisations), and two checklists: checklist hcorg-blue on topics related to the acquisition of new talent, and checklist hcorg-teal on organisational culture and processes

Title: Liberating Structures (EN)
Description: Liberating Structures want to offer an alternative way to approach and design how people work together. Their website contains a toolbox of 33 tools, combined with videos, audios and articles on different aspects of Liberating Structures.

Title: New Job Profiles within GIZ: The Digitalisation Partners
Description: The digitalisation partners are new positions at country offices. Digitalisation partners support their colleagues in data and IT security  + management issues and help navigate  the GIZ IT tool universe.

Title: New Roles within GIZ: The Digital Pioneers
Description: The Digital Pioneers are digitally competent GIZ employees supporting their colleagues in the digital transformation for 5-10 working days per year. Find out more about the Digital Pioneers on this website!

Title: Open Coop
Description: Open Coop is an online community and annual conference for individuals and organisations creating a collaborative, sustainable economy through openness and cooperation, instead of platform economies.

Title: Product Dartboard
Description: Product dartboard is an assessment and planning tool for software development teams, which can be tweaked to use it for other teams as well. It helps you identify your team’s strengths, challenges, and blind spots, so you can continuously improve the way your team works together.

Title: UK Government: Overview new job profiles in the digital age
Description: The Digital, Data and Technology Profession Capability Framework shows a directory of new job profiles and provides guidance on terms of reference.

Title: WEF: The Future of Jobs Report
Description: World Economic Forum report on the future of work and jobs in different regions and industries, as well as how to prepare the future workforce.

Title: League of Intrapreneurs
Description: The League of Intrapreneurs is a Global Learning community of intrapreneurs and catalysts working to unlock the human innovation potential inside influential institutions.

Title: Liberating Structures (DE)
Description: Liberating Structures wollen einen alternativen Weg anbieten, um die Zusammenarbeit zwischen den Menschen anzugehen und zu gestalten. Ihre Website enthält eine Toolbox mit 33 Tools, kombiniert mit Videos, Audios und Artikeln über verschiedene Aspekte von Liberating Structures.

Title: u.lab 2x
Description: This is a 4-month learning journey combining online and offline formats to enable participants to facilitate the transformation from ego to eco in social systems, which the authors regard as the number one leadership challenge of our time.

Title: The Future of Work: Preparing for Disruption
Description: Only MOOC to explore the 2019 World Development Report (WDR) and workforce of the future. Learn how AI, automation, advanced technologies and new businesses are changing the world.

Title: OSB International Systemic Consulting (EN)
Description: Newsletter, blog and consultancy following a systemic approach, focussing on leadership, strategy and organisational development, change and digital transformation with offices in Vienna, Hamburg, Cologne and Berlin.

Title: New Roles within GIZ: The Digital Pioneers
Description: The Digital Pioneers are digitally competent GIZ employees supporting their colleagues in the digital transformation for 5-10 working days per year. Find out more about the Digital Pioneers on this website!

Title: New Roles within GIZ: The Digital Pioneers
Description: The Digital Pioneers are digitally competent GIZ employees supporting their colleagues in the digital transformation for 5-10 working days per year. Find out more about the Digital Pioneers on this website!

Title: El futuro del trabajo y cómo prepararse para las disrupciones
Description: Basado en el Informe sobre el desarrollo mundial 2019, este nuevo curso del Banco Mundial explorará los diversos cambios derivados de los avances tecnológicos, qué significan estos para la actual y la futura fuerza laboral, y cómo debemos prepararnos para estos cambios.

Title: What is Holacracy? - Information & Courses
Description: Holacracy is a new way of structuring and running your organisation that replaces the conventional management hierarchy. Instead of operating top-down, power is distributed throughout the organisation, giving individuals and teams more freedom to self-manage, while staying aligned to the organisation’s purpose.

Title: Führungskompass
Description: Mit dem LEAD Führungskompass können Sie Ihre persönlichen Stärken und Führungsrollen analysieren und so Ihre Kompetenzen gezielt weiterentwickeln.

Title: Leadership Compass
Description: With the LEAD Leadership Compass you can analyse your personal strengths and leadership roles and thus develop your competencies in a targeted manner.

Title: Cooperation and Leadership Community
Description: What do cooperation and leadership look like? What potential does a different understanding of cooperation and leadership offer? Look around, share and join in the discussion. This community was initiated by the Cooperation and Leadership team (KuF).

Title: Cooperation and Leadership: New Work Academy
Description: The New Work Academy is a webinar series that features weekly conversations with GIZ’s most inspiring change makers and external industry leaders who believe in creating positive impact through agile methodologies and new forms of collaboration.

Title: Holacracy: A Radical New Approach to Management
Description: This TedTalk about Holacracy explains the radical new approach to management.

Title: Tandemploy: Tool for Knowledge Linking of Employees
Description: Tandemploy SaaS connects colleagues within your company for flexible forms of work, (new) forms of collaboration and topics of all kinds - and thus ensures a lively transfer of knowledge, the opening of silo structures, more innovative power and a higher competitiveness.

Title: ToolFest
Description: The Toolfest is an innovation festival where you will be able to meet future challenges by using your creative skills to solve problems - with the help of Design Thinking, New Work etc.

Title: Transformation Toolcamp (replaced by the Virtual Barcamp)
Description: The GIZ Transformation ToolCamp in Bonn is designed for you as a leader or facilitator in International Cooperation. If you are looking for a space to experiment or offer tools that support the journey through complexity: This is the place to meet up and start riding the digit-agile wave.

Title: Reverse Mentoring
Description: The community for reverse mentors is a space for sharing experiences and knowledge, for finding information and relevant documents, for networking and catching up on new developments.

Title: Kurse zur digitalen Kompetenz von Microsoft + Zertifikatstest
DigComp: EU Digital Competence Framework for Citizens
Description: The European Digital Competence Framework, also known as DigComp, offers a tool to improve citizen's digital competence. The support material includes a framework, infographics and open data interface.

Title: Digital Competence Wheel for Self-Assessment
Description: The purpose of the Digital Competence Wheel is to provide an overview of which digital competences exist and should be improved, as well as concrete inspiration for how to improve the most relevant digital competences. This tool has been developed by the Center for Digital Dannelse.

Title: Hyper Island Progress Index for Organizations
Description: Introductory assessment of your organisation's progress in digitalization. Based on this, Hyper Island offers courses and trainings (online and offline), diploma and masters degree courses as well as consultancy for digital transformation with global franchises and partners.

Title: Microsoft Digital Literacy Courses + Certificate
Competency Model of GIZ
Description: The Competency Model of GIZ provides orientation about the requirements for employees and managers in their entirety. It defines core competencies that contribute to the achievement of corporate goals and creates a uniform basis for personnel selection and development instruments.

Title: Europass Digital Competence
Description: Self-assessment in relation to digital competences is also part of the EU Europass. You can self-assess yourself in 3 competence levels within 5 fields of competence (data processing, content creation, communication, problem solving, security).

Title: GIZ Digital Literacy Compass
Description: The GIZ Digital Literacy Compass defines the relevant fields of digital skills for GIZ staff. All GIZ staff has the right to self-assess their skills level and will be granted learning time to acquire these skills, case they are missing.

Title: Cognizant Glossary
Description: Here you can find many key terms that define the digital economy, according to Cognizant.

Title: Digitization, Digitalization and Digital Transformation: The Differences
Description: Digitization, digitalization and digital transformation are three terms we use since many years but often in the wrong sense. This is an exploration of the differences as they do matter.

Title: Glossary Toolkit: Chapter 5
Description: In the fifth chapter of this toolkit you can find a glossary on digitalisation and sustainable development.

Title: LBBW: Key Terms of Digitalization and Industry 4.0
Description: This growing glossary from LLBW explains important specialist terms and provides an initial orientation for digital trends in a brief and comprehensible way.

Title: Agendashift Online: Learning the Language of Outcomes
Description: Online course with Mike Burrows which is open and framework-agnostic but combines approaches from Lean, Agile, organisation development (OD), and strategy deployment. This online course offers an introduction of tools which can be used in continuous change processes.

Title: Data Helpdesk of the KC Digital Society
Description: The Data Helpdesk at the FMB provides information on this intranet site about the consulting and information offers concerning the responsible handling of data in the context of project implementation.

Title: Data Protection Management within GIZ
Description: On the intranet site you will find everything relevant to the topics of data protection management.

Title: Digital Change in GIZ
Description: The intranet site of the Strategic Project Digital Change offers all necessary information on digital change within the GIZ with video tutorials and jumps to more detailed documents and information.

Title: Digital Gateway: GIZ Digital Pathfinder
Description: The Digital Pathfinder provides many examples of successful IT/digital projects and an excellent overview about the possibilities of employing ICT for development.

Title: Digitalisation at GIZ
Description: The target image of digital change describes in eight target dimensions (range of services, competences, leadership, cooperation, basis, workplace, organisation and processes), how GIZ wants to transform itself successfully in digital change.

Title: GIZ techDetector
Description: Technological innovations and their impact for international development is increasing as instruments for the achievement of the SDGs and as drivers of social, economic and organisational change. To fully use the potential of technological innovations, GIZ has developed the techDetector.

Title: How to be a Rock Star Project Manager on Digital Transformation
Description: This is a webinar for members of the PMI community - the largest community of project managers worldwide.

Title: The School of Future Learning: Interviews with Pioneers of Learning (EN)
Description: Interviews with inspiring people and pioneers, including talks about their role as role models and teachers.

Title: Board of Innovation: Innovation for Executives
Description: This is a 1-day training session for executives where you get to know how to enable innovation and accelerate growth by understanding what your teams are going through and how you can support them.

Title: Cours sur des compétences numériques
Description: Il s'agit d'une série de 6 cours disponible en français de Microsoft pour la formation en compétences IT et numériques, entre autres: connaissances numériques de base, communiquer en ligne, comment créer du contenu numérique, participer en ligne d'une manière responsable.

Title: Digital Gateway: Trend Topic The Future of Learning
Description: The trend topic The Future of Learning provides an overview of how we can learn today and in the future, as well as a deep immersion in the requirements of our workplace and living environment. You will also find other selected articles about podcasts, storytelling and learning hacks. Scroll down to read the english version.

Title: Learning-GIZ (EN)
Description: Via the online learning platform Learning GIZ you can find all further training courses offered by AIZ for GIZ employees as well as German implementing organisations and partners.

Title: Outil de formation (toolkit) à l'internet mobile
Description: Guide gratis de GSMA qui offre un outil de formation (toolkit) et 10 modules en vidéo à l'internet mobile (par exemple: présentation d'Internet, sécurité en ligne, réseaux sociaux etc.)

Title: Presentación del proyecto Digital Skills Accelerator (DSA)
Description: La plataforma del proyecto Digital Skills Accelerator presenta un plan de estudio que contendrá objetivos de aprendizaje detallados y niveles esperados de competencias digitales, divididos en 21 módulos en el marco de los 5 componentes clave de la competencia digital: Alfabetización informacional y de datos, Comunicación y colaboración, Creación de contenidos digitales, Seguridad y Solución de problemas.

Title: Beyond the Classroom! How to Hack Learning and How to Make It Fit for You and Your Colleagues? - Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: In this webinar we will have the opportunity to explore Learnhacks. They offer a collection of hands-on and down-to-earth exercises, tools, and routines empowering users to take ownership of their learning to become confident 21st century learners.

Title: Digital @DAI
Description: The consulting company DAI runs a blog with the digital topics they are working on, e.g. innovation, governance, environment and energy.

Title: Digital Learning Community
Description: The Community Digital Learning brings together people, knowledge, and methods to foster strategic competence development and implement digital learning tools within the project context. The Community provides a space to stay up-to-date and collaborate!

Title: Facilitation Skills for Networks, Gatherings and Conferences on- and offline - Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: This webinar is all about planning, facilitating and documenting engaging meetings, workshops, and gatherings on- and offline. Victoria Wenzelmann provides us with introductions and tools, and guided interactive sessions among the participants.

Title: How to facilitate interactive Online-Workshop?-  Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: In this webinar you will learn specific methods on how to design and facilitate an interactive online-workshop and how to actively engage your audience. In addition, Nikola Heidrich and Michael Tighe will provide you with some intercultural challenges you might encounter and overcome.

Title: Hyper Island: Driving Transformation
Description: Driving Transformation is an online course which teaches change management as well as the impacts of digitalisation on businesses and organisations to make learners fit for the digital transformation in their own organisations.

Title: Learnhacks (EN)
Description: Lernhacks GbR is a consulting company for enabling and building learning culture. On their website you can find helpful learnhacks which work like agile routines and smart tools that enable employees to proactively manage their professional development.

Title: Learning How to Learn
Description: This course gives you easy access to the invaluable learning techniques used by experts in art, music, literature, math, science, sports, and many other disciplines. You will learn about how the brain uses two very different learning modes and how it encapsulates (“chunks”) information.

Title: Podcasting: Start Quickly, Evolve Swiftly - Toolkit from the GIZ Digital Pioneer Community
Description: This webinar is all about podcasting. You’ll learn anything you need, to easily get started with your own podcast project. Nora Hespers will give a quick glimpse into the development of podcasts in the US and Germany and you will learn how to be the host or hostess of a compelling audio session.

Title: The 6 Creativity Hacks That Skyrocket Innovation
Description: In this article Bram van der Lecq reveals surprising results of his master thesis. The question: Do employees perceive a relationship between creativity and emotions in the organisational context and how does this influence their creativity?

Title: What is Working Out Loud?
Description: What is Working Out Loud? It's a 12-week program of co-creation in a safe environment.

Title: Working Out Loud – The Making of a Movement
Description: Do you want to make a difference in your life? In your organisation? In the world? Working Out Loud can help you. In his TedTalk John Stepper explains how to work out loud.

Title: Mobile Internet Skills Training Toolkit by GSMA
Description: This is a free guide for training people in basic mobile internet skills by GSMA. It contains a complete set for trainers from How to create your training to training sessions checklists, posters and hangouts on mobile social media.

Title: PMI Project Management Institute
Description: The PMI community is the largest community of project managers worldwide. After registration you get free webinars, articles, knowledge boards, templates, etc.

Title: Scrum Alliance: Scrum Foundations eLearning Series
Description: 14-part eLearning series, based on the Scrum Guide and broken out into sections of 5 minutes maximum length.

Title: Scrum.org
Description: Global programme offering trainings, information and certifications for different roles. Scrum.org was founded by Ken Schwaber, author of the Scrum Guide. Self-assessment through the Open Assessments is possible before taking a course and paying for a certificate.

Title: Team Human Podcast
Description: Podcast, book and blog by author, media theorist, and professor Douglas Rushkoff whose work focusses on the relationship between humanity and technology, and reprogramming society to better serve humans. He invites different guests for his podcast with each episode being a dialogue on one topic.

Title: Thoughtworks: Tech Radar
Description: Thoughtworks Tech Radar is one of the most insightful publications analyzing trends in technology. It is published roughly every 6 months, and is in its 21st edition now.

Title: Trendradar of the Betterplace Lab (DE)
Description: The trendradar of the betterplace lab, a Berlin-based digital-social think tank, provides and insight into the current relevant trends in Digital4Development.

Title: Nesta: A Brief Introduction to Digital Transformation
Description: A guide for public sector leaders who want to understand and get the best out of technology.

Title: Open HPI (EN)
Description: Courses offered by HPI, the pioneers of Design Thinking in Germany, and one of the hubs of digital innovation. In the Open HPI courses, the teachers and experts of HPI share their knowledge with everyone

Title: Betterplace Lab (EN)
Description: The betterplace lab is a digital-social think-and-do tank.

Title: MOOD
Description: No Description

Title: Virtual Barcamp
Description: No Description
